The mission of vrtk was to galvanise a community to solve common vr problems together and to open up vr creation to a new generation of creators, open source is the only real way for that.

People are able to pay for it now if they want via patreon. But then why would people pay if they can get it free from github and removing it from github removes the open source ethos which is at the core of vrtk

As suggested here above, sell it as an asset albeit more cheaply maybe $4.99, some may see that as a paywall but most would pay that. I'm sure VRTK has been DL a lot from the asset store? so multiples of a small fee would add up.
I've tried a lot of avenues, all have been dead ends, I can't keep putting effort into dead ends. That's the unfortunate reality. Better to finish up and move on than flog a dead horse.

$2.5k a month in patreon isn't close. Once you take fees, exchange rates into consideration then that's like £1.4k a month, that's only £18k a year, which isn't nearly enough to cover the costs of the plans

The mission of VRTK was to provide a way to get as many people building for vr as possible, a pay wall would immediately hamper that. Besides people could have paid monthly now via patreon and that didn't make nearly enough.
Why not sell it as a Unity asset? We'd pay $10-20/month for it. I bet most VR devs would too.

I had previously done a Kickstarter which failed to meet its goal. The patreon came off the back of that with the general consensus saying it would be better (I never thought it was a good funding idea).
How much do you need to keep it going? Put up a pledge drive, people like goals :) I have to imagine most VR dev (us included) would be happy to pay. Patreon always felt like the wrong format.
